Istanbul Inflation Rises to 2.51 Percent in April, Group Says

-- B y   A l i   B e r a t   M e r i c
-- 
2011-05-01T10:19:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-01/istanbul-inflation-rises-to-2-51-percent-in-april-group-says.html
The monthly inflation rate in
Istanbul,  Turkey ’s biggest city, rose to 2.51 percent in April,
the city’s chamber of commerce said.  Annual inflation in Istanbul was 4.63 percent in April,
according to the e-mailed statement from the chamber. Turkey’s
state statistics agency will announce nationwide price data for
April on May 3.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ali Berat Meric in Ankara at 
 americ@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
